# 🏙️ City Research Assistant

A beginner-friendly Streamlit application that helps users compare two cities
before relocating — e.g. "Should I move to Pune or Bengaluru?" — using
**Smolagents** for multi-agent orchestration and 4 real, free data APIs.

---

## 🏗️ Agent Architecture

```
                            User
                             │
                             ▼
                  Streamlit Chat Interface
                             │
                             ▼
                   Coordinator Agent (LLM)
                             │
           ┌────────────────┼────────────────┬────────────────┐
           ▼                ▼                ▼                ▼
   Amenities Agent    Weather Agent   Web Research Agent  Book Rec. Agent
           │                │                │                │
           ▼                ▼                ▼                ▼
  OpenStreetMap/Nominatim  Open-Meteo      Tavily API      Open Library API
           │                │                │                │
           └────────────────┴───── (run in TRUE parallel) ────┘
                             │
                             ▼
                    Comparison Agent (LLM)
                             │
                             ▼
              Final City Recommendation
```

**Only two steps use an LLM**: the Coordinator (extracting cities/priorities
from your question) and the Comparison Agent (synthesizing the final
recommendation). The four research agents are pure Python/`requests` calls
against real APIs — they never call an LLM, and the Comparison Agent is
explicitly instructed never to invent numbers that aren't in the data it
was given.

